.rpm based distros

* YUM * 
$ yum <options>

search - search for the exact name of a package
provides - look for specific files within the available packages
info - provide more information about the package
install - dont need to write about this one
remove - same here
list [all | installed] - list all or installed packages
group [list, info, etc)
group install - install all packages from a group
update - update packages specified
clean all - remove all stored metadata
history - diplay history of yum usage
history undo <number> - undo the associated activity 

> Manage Module Streams:

$ yum module info <packagename>:<version>/<profile>
$ yum module reset <modulename>
$ yum module install <packagename>:<version>/<profile> --allowerasing
$ yum module enable <packagename>:<version>

$ yum distro-sync
^ ensure all dependent packages are updated

To ensure that all dependent packages are updated as well > $ yum distro-sync

* RPM - Querying - Managing Software Package *
$ rpm <options>

qd - query docs files
qc - query configuration fiels
q --scripts - query if there is

$ repoquery <options looks similar to rpm command>

obs: install "yum-utils" to use $ yumdownloader
^ downloads a package without installing 




